               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I took up the book - I looked at it two or three minutes; I placed it under my arm, and looked at another - I meant to bring this one in and ask the price, but I put down the other and forgot the book under my arm; I walked away, and it fell down - I took it up, the prosecutor came and said I had not paid for it: I had but 9d. - he said it was 2s. 6d.</p>
